# Privacy Policy

Last Updated: June 2026

Thank you for playing Stack City.

This Privacy Policy explains how information may be collected and used when you play our game.

## Information We Collect

Stack City does not collect personal information such as your name, email address, phone number, or home address.

Third-party services used by the game, such as advertising and analytics providers, may automatically collect limited information including:

* Device type
* Operating system version
* Advertising identifiers
* Gameplay statistics
* Crash reports
* General location information (country or region)

## Advertising

Stack City may display advertisements provided by third-party advertising partners.

These partners may use advertising identifiers to provide and measure advertisements. We do not control how third-party advertising services collect or process information.

## Analytics

We may use analytics services to understand how players use the game, improve performance, and fix issues.

Analytics data is collected in an anonymous or aggregated form whenever possible.

## Children's Privacy

Stack City is not directed toward children under the age required by applicable laws in their region.

If you believe personal information has been collected from a child inappropriately, please contact us so that appropriate action can be taken.

## Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect information used by the game. However, no method of electronic storage or transmission is completely secure.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted within the game store listing or associated website.

